  "text": "[20] The total area containing near-surface permafrost (poleward of 45°N) is listed for all experiments in Table 2 . For the period 1970 -1989, the area in the original coupled simulation is 9.5 Â 10 6 km 2 (note that this is lower than the value of 10.5 Â 10 6 km 2 reported by Lawrence and Slater [2005] because it includes only land area north of 45°N and represents only a single ensemble member, whereas [CITATION_1] reported the fivemember ensemble average areal extent). The area in CONTROL CLM3 is a bit lower at 9.0 Â 10 6 km 2 , reflecting the biases related to the experimental design that are discussed in section 2.2.",
